#: ../../W/weenie.rst:5
msgid "weenie"
msgstr "weenie"

#: ../../W/weenie.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../W/weenie.rst:10
msgid ""
"[on BBSes] Any of a species of luser resembling a less amusing version of "
":ref:`B1FF` that infests many :ref:`BBS` systems. The typical weenie is a "
"teenage boy with poor social skills travelling under a grandiose "
":ref:`handle` derived from fantasy or heavy-metal rock lyrics. Among sysops,"
" the weenie problem refers to the marginally literate and profanity-laden "
":ref:`flamage` weenies tend to spew all over a newly-discovered BBS. Compare"
" :ref:`spod`\\, :ref:`geek`\\, :ref:`terminal-junkie`\\, "
":ref:`warez-d00dz`\\."
msgstr ""
"[BBS上で] \\ :ref:`B1FF`\\ のあまり面白くない版に似た、多くの\\ :ref:`BBS`\\ "
"システムにはびこるluserの一種。典型的なweenieは、社会的技能に乏しく、ファンタジーやヘヴィメタルのロックの歌詞から派生した大げさな\\ "
":ref:`handle`\\ "
"を名乗る10代の少年である。sysopの間では、weenie問題とは、weenieが新たに発見したBBSの至るところにまき散らしがちな、かろうじて読める程度で冒涜的な\\"
" :ref:`flamage`\\ を指す。\\ :ref:`spod`\\ 、\\ :ref:`geek`\\ 、\\ :ref:`terminal-"
"junkie`\\ 、\\ :ref:`warez-d00dz`\\ と比較せよ。"

#: ../../W/weenie.rst:16
msgid ""
"[among hackers] When used with a qualifier (for example, as in :ref:`Unix-"
"weenie`\\, VMS weenie, IBM weenie) this can be either an insult or a term of"
" praise, depending on context, tone of voice, and whether or not it is "
"applied by a person who considers him or herself to be the same sort of "
"weenie. Implies that the weenie has put a major investment of time, effort, "
"and concentration into the area indicated; whether this is good or bad "
"depends on the hearer's judgment of how the speaker feels about that area. "
"See also :ref:`bigot`\\."
msgstr ""
"[ハッカーの間で] 限定詞とともに使われる場合(たとえば\\ :ref:`Unix-weenie`\\ 、VMS weenie、IBM "
"weenieのように)、これは侮辱にも称賛の言葉にもなりうる。文脈、声の調子、そしてそれが自分自身を同種のweenieだと考える人物によって適用されるかどうかによる。weenieが指定された分野に時間、労力、集中の大きな投資を注いだことを含意する。これが良いか悪いかは、話し手がその分野についてどう感じているかについての聞き手の判断による。\\"
" :ref:`bigot`\\ も参照。"

